Package assignment.trip

Class Trip

java.lang.Object
assignment.trip.Trip
public class Trip extends Object
This class represents a trip between two PLANETS.

Each trip contains:
  • the starting planet
  • the destination planet
  • the vehicle
  • the distance of the trip
  • the speed of the vehicle
  • the amount of time needed for the trip
  • the cost of paying each crew member per day
  • the cost of feeding each member of the crew per day
  • the total cost of paying the entire crew
  • the total cost of feeding the entire crew
  • the total gross income of the entire crew (pay and food costs)

  • Constructor Summary

    Constructors
    Constructor
    Description
    Trip(PlanetaryBody startingPlanet, PlanetaryBody destinationPlanet, TransportationVehicle vehicle, double tripDistance, double vehicleSpeed)
    Instantiates a Trip object using the given parameters.

    This constructor also uses the ScientificCalc class to determine the travel duration, as well as the SpaceTravelFinancing class to determine the total amount of money paid to each crew member and the total amount of money paid to the entire crew.
    Trip(PlanetaryBody startingPlanet, PlanetaryBody destinationPlanet, TransportationVehicle vehicle, double tripDistance, double vehicleSpeed, LocalDate departDate)
    Instantiates a Trip object using the given parameters.

    This constructor also uses the ScientificCalc class to determine the travel duration, as well as the SpaceTravelFinancing class to determine the total amount of money paid to each crew member and the total amount of money paid to the entire crew.
